cs.SE, cs.CE, cs.CY, cs.LG, cs.HC 

This paper discusses experiences from a classroom project where students developed a software system using Scrum, which is a popular agile methodology in software engineering. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also discusses the use of surveys and tutors to assess Scrum adoption, which could fall under cs.CE (Computational Engineering), cs.CY (Computers and Society), or cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of tool-supported analysis of collaboration artifacts, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
